social_posts.post_text: Happy Heavenly Birthday to one of my heroes. Jay Dee. Thank you so much for blessing us with your immense gift and for lifting the hearts and souls of so many with your unrelenting genius and your visionary beats. Lawd. So wish I could’ve met you. Grateful to know and be inspired by your work. #jdilla #jdillachangedmylife #jdilladonuts #jaydee #jamesyancy #jamesdewittyancey #blackgenius #producersmatter #detroit #detroitsown #detroitsfinest #donuts #donutsdonutsdonuts #donutsareforever 🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🍩🙏🏽

Guess what? 
Weeeee’re baaaaaaaack!

As part of his swan song as Program Director @paristheaternyc @davidpschwartz has programmed some 2020 releases for his most illustrious exit and #fyov #fortyyearoldversionfilm is a part of this awesome curation. So for those looking to see it on the big screen, you’re in luck! 

We may even do a lil talk back or something. Stay tuned!!!

Thanks David. Grateful FYOV was a part of your tenure at one of my favorite nyc childhood jaunts.

social_posts.post_text:
Congratulations to my good sister friends director @misscortes and executive producer #deerees on the amazing doc #littlerichardiameverything. And sharing it in Harlem at the historic @schomburgcenter. We laughed we cried we marveled at this beautiful look into the life and legacy of one our luminary Black trailblazers. I thought I knew. I learned so much. And can’t wait to see it again. Lisa I’m so effn proud and inspired by this work! Keep soaring mama! 

I love when asked what your fave Little Richard song was you said “Keep A Knockin’” because it represents his struggle and challenge to get “in” but we all know his super power was being an outsider. 

#blackwomendirectors #blackwomenfilmmakers #blackwomenstorytellers #madebyablackwoman #littlerichard #shutup

Opens April 21st in theaters!
Proud card-carrying member since 2014. #wgastrong✊🏽✊🏼✊🏾✊🏿 #fuckyoupayme

Muvah. 
Goddess. 
Sorceress.
Alien. 
Anomaly of the Universe. 
One of one. 
Grateful to bare witness to your genius. 
(And with my sisters too)
Molecules shifted.
Grace.
You owe us nothing.
Thank you and Gods mercies.
Phew.

🖤🖤🖤

Bowie. Here’s to your first year of life! You’ve been such a gift to my heart. I don’t think I’ve EVER laughed this much. You’re such a special soul. Just what I needed sweet girl. Grateful to all your besties (“I’m in love wit da Coco!”) and their dog parents. So thankful for your aunties and uncles for dog sitting, being a supportive community and talking me “off the ledge”, giving sage advice and getting you gifts, treats and so much LOVE! BUT biggest thanks to my cousin @twilder77 for sitting me down that day (probably on The Baylander lol) and talking me out of my fear. “Get the damn dog already! It’ll be good for you!” How right you were Trace. I may have called #bidawee in tears ten times those first weeks thinking I’d take you back but now I can’t imagine life without you. Bowie Iman, I Love you “dawgter”. #july9 #bowieblank #bowieiman #dawgter #blackdogmoms

We made it on the jumbo tron! #newyorkliberty #lasvegasaces #wnba #womenballers🏀 #loveandbasketball #nydreams #ilovemycity❤️ 🗽

@thecoolidge 
Come join us! Link in bio!

In celebration of the groundbreaking cultural movement that has inspired generations, this August, the Coolidge is thrilled to present a robust program of 20 films highlighting 50 years of hip hop’s undeniable influence on cinema.

🎤 "Been Here for Years: Hip Hop at 50" is co-presented by @mubi, @masshiphoparchive, and @thehiphoparchive! Throughout August, we're highlighting documentaries, concert films, biopics, and dramas, hosting discussions with filmmakers and special guests along the way! See the full lineup in our story and get tickets at coolidge.org/hiphop.

How freaking cool is this? Thanks so much to @arjunchadha1 and the good fam at @getfamiliarmag for this awesome profile on ya sis. Great, transparent convo here! And supercharged to be included amongst such powerful artists profiled in this great zine exploring the global impact and diaspora of Hip Hop culture.

Happy Birthday to meeeeeeee! (Part one) For the 9/24, I got to do something I always wanted to do: put my big tatas in the wiiiind! Thank you to my brave, loving and awesome heart soldiers for taking the plunge with me. I love you guys soooo much! I laughed so much and really connected with my inner child. And thanks @flybyallmeans for the great instruction, patient guidance and lifting my big arse into the air making me look graceful af. You rock and you inspired us to maybe one day do some real sky dancing like you!

Happy Birthday to meeeeeee (Part 2) 

Just so grateful for the amazing people in my life. If I was to ever doubt my power and beauty i can always look to see my spirit reflected in yours. Thank you to those who came out for a celebratory sip and those who couldn’t make it but extended such loving bday messages and gifts. And thanks to that special special soul who shared that one of a kind geriatric gift pack- “payback is a muhfka, believe me!” 🤣🤣🤣

A NEW YORK NIGHT!!! @nyliberty did the damn thang! 84-77!!! And I got to bare witness of this triumph with such luminaries including THEE #franlebowitz. Wow Bday week has been EPIC! Congrats to this awesome team of Warrior Kwangs! 🗽🏀⛹🏽‍♀️🪽💥
